                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Steering Committee/511: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Norman H. Davis</persName> at London</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-21T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 21, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 16, 2 p.m. I consider the progress made in the conversation you report
                    to be highly satisfactory.</p>
                <p>With regard to our taking up with Italy the matter of their not departing from
                    the provisions of the 1936 Naval Treaty, I would see no-objection to our doing
                    so if you were to recommend such an approach.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
